caption.text:
A piece of advice from me, to those of you who are trying to be happy.
.
It's been about a year since I graduated high school. And I learned a lot things I didn't learn there. I learned about opportunities, hardworking, making choices, meeting new friends and keeping old ones, appreciating little things, love, time management, family, and even losing someone.
But most of all, I learned a lot about acceptance. I finally understood and fully accepted that I cannot control the universe. I cannot control fate. Sometimes bad things just happen, and it's out of our control. But sometimes, I will get the opportunity to do something that matters, even if it's just a tiny thing like making someone smile or watering my plants or feeding my fish. I accepted that each of us is just a tiny speck of stardust in this immense existance, and I accepted my insignificance. But at the same time, understood my absolute importance. And when bad things do happen, I can ask myself this question: 'Can I do something to make it better?' If yes, then I would go ahead and do it. If no, then just accept it. Don't waste any energy stressing over a thing we can't change. 
And I learned that, when I accepted myself and everything else around me, I'm fully content. As a matter of fact, I've been blissfully happy. And of course I won't always be happy all the time, but it's okay because that's just the way it is. So I intend to enjoy life while I can. We only live once. Please try to make every single second count.
-16.05.28
